# TypeScript Standards

- Enable strict mode; no `any` without a one-line justification comment.
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; use `type` for unions and Zod inferred types.
- Export shared types from `lib/types/`; don't duplicate API shapes in components.

```typescript
// BAD
const product: any = await getProduct(slug);

// GOOD
const product: ProductWithVariants = await productService.getBySlug(slug);
```

- Use `satisfies` for config objects; narrow errors with custom classes (`OrderNotFoundError`).
- Async: always handle rejection; never floating promises in event handlers.
- Import order: external -> `@/` aliases -> relative.
